commit 646f833a39c89cc6412eb4260366f5c86bf6b790
Author: Brian Bidulock <bidulock@openss7.org>
Date:   Thu Nov 14 12:23:24 2013 -0700

    add WM_WINDOW_ROLE to selection and check windows

     When there are two top-level windows with the same WM_NAME, WM_CLASS
     and WM_COMMAND values, there needs to be a differing WM_WINDOW_ROLE
     property to distinguish the windows.  We give the WM_S%d selection
     owner window the role "selection" and the _NET_SUPPORTING_WM_CHECK
     window the role "check".

 src/Screen.cc | 36 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-------
 1 file changed, 29 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

