commit 95f1e30fde8177f7cc4b58836f88ad714d309d16
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Wed Dec 22 10:22:40 2004 +0000

    1. when doing an opaque resize, the maximize flag should be cleared
    when the resize starts, not when it finishes

    2. when finishing a non-opaque resize, clearing the maximize flag
    should be done before setting client.state.resizing to false.  this
    prevents the window from flickering (due to the window first being
    restored and then resized to the new location)

 src/Window.cc | 20 +++++++++++++-------
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

