commit 991cf4a0bf1453110cc933112fa5b579f8d5e3c0
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Mon Aug 30 18:04:54 2004 +0000

    Add support for UTF-32 as well as UTF-8... UTF-32 will be used throughout
    the API where we need to do character operations (like bt::ellideText)
    using
    the bt::ustring type.  Conversions to/from locale, UTF-8 and UTF-32
    are done
    using iconv(3).

    Prepare to rename Utf8.* to Unicode.*

