commit d22ad562bf2548c25bb8a7363c5f6ef50a943040
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Thu Jul 8 13:07:42 2004 +0000

    don't use a synchronous grab during menu handling... it's not really
    necessary, and the last replay doesn't seem to work 100%

    this results in a slight change in behavior, when clicking outside a
    menu to close it, the click is no longer forwarded, it is discarded.
    this means it is possible to click ANYWHERE on the screen to dismiss a
    menu, without having to worry about what is under the pointer

 lib/Application.cc | 9 ++-------
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

