 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

commit fbd30820da99904cbb516da719263ad9151d8398
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Tue Jun 22 15:47:05 2004 +0000

    for clarity, change *.Margin -> *.MarginWidth in ToolBar and Slit
    styles (to be consistent with bt::Menu)

 src/BlackboxResource.cc | 8 ++++----
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

commit 00e17ffb288e5c671adb7c5a043abf33474456b0
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Mon Jun 21 15:10:35 2004 +0000

    don't crash if we select an item in a menu while a submenu is open.

    to do this, we track the current submenu and active submenu
    separately.  the current submenu (_current_submenu) is the submenu
    that is currently visible.	the active submenu (_active_submenu) is
    the submenu for the active item.

    this makes the logic a bit easier to understand (for me at least)

 lib/Menu.cc | 66 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-------------------
 lib/Menu.hh |	1 +
 2 files changed, 45 insertions(+), 22 deletions(-)

commit 9c4f329d7c67933f5222f753b352b5a3519ff7f8
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Mon Jun 21 14:05:07 2004 +0000

    don't process ConfigureRequest events using the normal
    bt::EventHandler mechanism in bt::Application, since event is sent to
    the window that selected for redirect (not the window that requested
    the event).

    this solves a race in where a ConfigureRequest is issued after a
    MapRequest, but before blackbox has had a change to reparent the
    client to the window frame... this configure request was passed to
    BScreen, which blindly accepted the request (so that the client is
    reconfigured while inside the frame)

    it's not a good idea to handle any of the *Request events in
    bt::Application, so we do this in Blackbox::process_events()

    see bug 972731

 lib/Application.cc  |	5 -----
 lib/EventHandler.hh |	3 ---
 src/Screen.cc	     | 25 -------------------------
 src/Screen.hh	     |	1 -
 src/blackbox.cc     | 30 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 5 files changed, 30 insertions(+), 34 deletions(-)

