commit 91cc240a3b95bd52de5941f94a6fdd420bfbc42c
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Tue Jun 1 09:45:06 2004 +0000

    Transients must be on the same screen as their parent.  This prevents
    crashes when using (for example) Konqueror on a multi-screen display,
    where the browser is on screen 1 and various dialogs are shown on
    screen 0.

 src/Window.cc | 7 ++++++-
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

commit 491bd8ea5bb72538bbd026c8b7a6b864138fb1fb
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Thu Mar 18 09:38:14 2004 +0000

    remove HAVE_PROCESS_H, we don't use this type of detection anymore...

 lib/Util.cc | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

commit c701a36b63addc8fe03043c384b8c5d4826d5275
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Tue Mar 9 15:38:44 2004 +0000

    after some thought and reading POSIX, it seems pointless for us to
    trap fatal signals... they are fatal for a reason :)

    rename the FATAL_SIGNAL run state to SIGNALLED, which is set when we
    call bt::Application::process_signal()...  the run state is reset to
    RUNNING if process_signal returns true and the run_state has not been
    changed.  we still dump core when running into unhandled (aka unknown)
    signals.

    this should ensure that libbt users will have sane and proper signal
    handling

 lib/Application.cc | 47 +++++++++++++++++++----------------------------
 lib/Application.hh |  2 +-
 2 files changed, 20 insertions(+), 29 deletions(-)

commit e90ab639eafaaad0cd642eb7a7635549c944bc67
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Tue Mar 9 09:59:14 2004 +0000

    when a client's XA_WM_NORMAL_HINTS change, we need to constrain the
    current geometry to the new min-size, max-size, base-size, size-inc
    and aspect-ratio...

    this fixes bug 893468 where xmms wouldn't properly shade/unshade

