commit 30e5c81a633ce582489e0b7d5c55cfb41e01b308
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Fri Jan 9 12:07:12 2004 +0000

    add the EWMH struct which holds all of the state information needed
    for EWMH support... rename getNetwmHints() to readEWMH(), which
    returns an instance of EWMH

    work on more EWMH compliance:

    - support all window types: each window type is decorated a certain
      way to both indicate and facilitate its use.  the
      update_decorations() in Window.cc was added as a way of quickly and
      easily getting the decorations/functions for a specific window based
      on its type and other properties.

    - enforce certain behavior for certain window types:

      desktop/dock windows will neither receive focus when managed nor
      when the mouse moves over them in sloppy-focus-mode, and they occupy
      all workspaces by default

      desktop windows are placed in their own special stacking layer,
      while dock windows are placed in the above layer

      WindowFunctionChangeWorkspace is disabled for all
      transients... these should be kept on the same workspace as their
      parent

      KillClient is disable in the window menu for transients, to prevent,
      for example, the possibility of killing an entire application
      instead of simply closing a dialog

 COMPLIANCE    |  14 +-
 src/Screen.cc |  19 +-
 src/Window.cc | 606 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-------------------------
 src/Window.hh |  76 ++++---
 4 files changed, 383 insertions(+), 332 deletions(-)

