commit 7e38f88c9b012b51e66995a1b5e985d25385fa3a
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Thu Jan 8 12:06:55 2004 +0000

    add the MotifHints struct to BlackboxWindow, which holds the desired
    functions and decorations as set by the client... we use this to mask
    away the stuff not wanted by the application (instead of using it
    exactly as specified).  this is the best mix of EWMH and MWM hints
    that I can think of...

    rename getMWMHints to readMotifHints(), which returns an instead of
    MotifHints...

    fix a race/memleak caused by not removing frame.plate from the
    Window->BlackboxWindow* mapper... the memleak is small, but can become
    noticable if you open and close lots of windows... i found this due to
    a race using 'Kill Client' from the window menu... sometimes i would
    get a button release on the plate, which mapped to a dangling
    BlackboxWindow* (since the window was destroyed by a previous
    DestroyWindow event resulting from the KillClient)

