commit 9c61d2e9792fd34fec0b55dd90997f271d377b16
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Wed Jan 7 15:10:22 2004 +0000

    add a WMHints struct to contain the information in the WM_HINTS
    property and expose this struct through the public API (redundant API
    was subsequently removed)

      some code was adjusted to use the new struct over the old way of
      doing things. in particular, we no longer rely on the current state
      of a newly managed window to be set to the initial state, instead we
      use the initial state directly in BScreen::manageWindow() (this is
      both cleaner and clearer about what is going on).  note: this change
      does not change functionality

    rename getWMHints() to readWMHints() which returns a WMHints struct

