commit 13537fbf4793ffe9a6201e3f3b9c802401b50112
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Mon Jan 5 13:36:41 2004 +0000

    it seems that gcc tries to inline default constructors/destructors for
    structs and classes, but complains if inlining fails...  this happens
    here, where large numbers of strings are being constructed... so we
    define out-of-line constructors and destructors to pacify gcc

