    instead, falling back to Xft... this should keep old styles working on
    Xft enabled builds

 lib/Font.cc | 68 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++--------------------
 1 file changed, 44 insertions(+), 24 deletions(-)

commit 65f8c83f723f74cbeff35e42da8cb2bd9d83ea7e
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Fri Jan 2 15:27:07 2004 +0000

    honor program specified position again... ignoring this causes more
    problems than it solves (and it seems many window managers have made
    the same mistake).

    for compatibility, always honor the motif window manager hints if they
    are present... to many programs rely on this working, and some seem to
    mix EWMH and MWM stuff together, making matters worse.  once the EWMH
    is more widespread, we can completely remove the MWM code, but until
    then we wait...

 src/Screen.cc | 13 ++++++------
 src/Window.cc | 63 +++++++++++++++++++++++--------------------------------
 2 files changed, 33 insertions(+), 43 deletions(-)

