commit 6ef8cbe4c1740fe8bb12699427b6837a01bff7b3
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Fri Nov 28 10:45:50 2003 +0000

    cleanup: use references to the end iterator where possible

    when removing multiple items in an itemClicked() reimplementation, it
    is possible to actually move past the end iterator... this is not
    good, so forget about using the 'once' variable in
    buttonReleaseEvent() to stop multiple activation... use 'break;'
    instead... much more reliable...

