commit 7ba1bf34500e5dec0c86cd4d6ec1c5bce1f79cda
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Sat Nov 15 21:44:30 2003 +0000

    1. move the window and stacking lists from Workspace to BScreen.  this
    requires moving most of the functionality in Workspace to BScreen as
    well:
    - window placement
    - window stacking
    - focus fallback

    2. introduce StackEntity and use it in the stacking list... this
    allows us to have the Slit and Toolbar as proper stack participants.

    3. finish the layered stacking support... this means that we can have
    as many different layers as we want... currently we implement the
    following:
      - fullscreen
      - always-on-top
      - normal
      - always-on-bottom
      - desktop

    we now expose the always-on-top and always-on-bottom layers to the
    end-user through the Windowmenu

    4. implement smart full-screen support - when a focused full-screen
    window is raised, it is placed above all other windows (including
    windows marked always-on-top).  when it looses focus, it is moved to
    the always-on-bottom layer.  raising the window will again bring it on
    top of everything else.

    5. cleanup BlackboxWindow and BScreen API to be more concise, easier
    to understand and use.

    6. many bugs and cleanups are also included in this commit... they
    were a necessary part of completing the above changes and making sure
    the new functionality is working

 src/Clientmenu.cc   |	 27 +-
 src/Iconmenu.cc     |	  5 +-
 src/Screen.cc	     | 1016 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++----------
