 3 files changed, 163 insertions(+), 169 deletions(-)

commit 3b664803e933a43ddb4e5e54fa5540b2c81fa7f5
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Fri Nov 14 15:48:38 2003 +0000

    1. use more descriptive parameter names for BlackboxWindow::setWorkspace()

    2. change the way we handle GloballyActive and NoInput windows.
    before we would simply refuse to focus these windows... HOWEVER, in
    the case of GloballyActive, the client would expect us to send a
    WM_TAKE_FOCUS message (and indicate to the user that the window is
    active).  it would then move focus to some child window (we don't care
    about that part though).

    what does this mean?

    first: things like xload can now become active... this is not in
    violation of the ICCCM, since we don't explicitly set focus to the
    xload window, instead we set it to the plate (the parent of the client
    window).  this allows you to, for example, use bbkeys to
    close/move/shade/etc. with the keyboard (since it is the active
    window).

    second: this should allow things like nautilus to behave properly.	I
    haven't not tested this, but since nautilus is a GloballyActive
    client, we need to allow users to focus it and do useful things with
    it.

 src/Window.cc | 52 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++----------------------
 src/Window.hh |  2 +-
 2 files changed, 31 insertions(+), 23 deletions(-)

commit a950156927e8daa4a687341006253c97901c7078
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Fri Nov 14 15:13:00 2003 +0000

    stylistic changes

 src/Configmenu.cc | 9 ++++++---
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

commit 68dd825de9391c3f96b4e66ce2f5284503cefc70
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
