commit 1a0c318ef632431299102dfc7079ab0357185fe9
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Fri Oct 17 08:20:31 2003 +0000

    move bt::normalizeTimeval to Timer.hh, this is the more appropriate
    place for this function.

    add bt::timeval, which is a wrapper around the POSIX timeval type.
    use bt::timeval throughout the API, relying on implicit POSIX<->bt
    conversions

    this should get bt::Timer working on more compilers now.  I have
    tested this with gcc 2.95.4, gcc 3.3.1 and icc 7.1

