commit d6743dacee325625b85843db7d2d2c98d9bf3a5e
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Mon Jun 23 08:03:40 2003 +0000

    require a sane POSIX-compliant system for blackbox... this way we can
    get rid of this sys/time.h and time.h madness

    also, gcc 2.95.x doesn't seem to like only the forward declaration of
    the timeval struct, so we have to include sys/time.h in Timer.hh
    (unfortunately)

