commit be65b6a7eb5a30221db614f824cf40bc8fd5b603
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Mon Jun 23 07:45:13 2003 +0000

    according to POSIX-1003.1, sscanf() expects the "%f" to be a float.
    we should use "%lf" for double.  this is completely different from
    *printf(), which assumes "%f" is a double (not a float).

 lib/Resource.cc | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

