commit 916dfb4660c83467cf61d1d73444e28ce9d7052a
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Mon Apr 28 15:09:46 2003 +0000

    don't really need to uninstall the colormap when loosing focus.  we should
    only ever need to install colormaps... on hardware that supports multiple
    colormaps, we don't want to remove the colormap just because a window
    is not focused.

 src/Window.cc | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

commit a29fdb961494b895a6bfd767cfa5dde40971d93a
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Mon Apr 28 14:21:22 2003 +0000

    get window/screen colormap handling working again.

    the old code was a tad incorrect.  Section 9.3 of the Xlib manual was
    quite helpful, it explains that the X server does lots of magic for
    us, so all we need to really do is tell it which colormaps we want to
    use.

