commit 119e74b1c48988d52b89ca8fe8997cfefcb61497
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Mon Mar 24 16:07:29 2003 +0000

    SubstructureNotify on the root window is absolutely pointless,
    regardless of how many other window managers do it.

    in my opinion, StructureNotify is equally pointless, but it seems some
    applications assume that the window manager listens for
    StructureNotify events on the root window.	for the moment,
    StructureNotify can stay, but I hope to see this gone.

 src/Screen.cc | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

