commit df2b6fd3f67e609717cbf401d2d81212b0948321
Author: shaleh <shaleh>
Date:	Wed Feb 5 16:26:34 2003 +0000

    Reduced the size of the BlackboxWindow class by 54 bytes or 13%.
    352 bytes are
    used per instance now.  This was accomplished by a) removing the foo_pixel
    data members which were no longer used due to changes in the Texture
    class and
    b) moving several of the frame size members into the window's style.  There
    was no reason to repeat the same math over and over for every window
    when they
    all used the same values.  Along the way 34 lines of crufty code were also
    removed.

    Now for the controversial part (-:	I changed the style attribute
    "window.handle_width" to "window.handle_height".  This matches the
    convention
    used elsewhere.  Another possible name would be "handle_thickness".
    The style
    converter has been updated to match this change as well as the styles
    themselves.

