commit 5af1d09231b74ce6211a1ac1d3e4114d346930de
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Wed Jan 15 11:00:35 2003 +0000

    1) add support for the MIT-SHM extension.  use it for rendering images
       smaller than 480000 (400x300 @ 32-bit color) bytes to improve
       performance.  anything over the above size is rendered the normal
       way.

    2) change the way bt::Image stores image data.  instead of having
    3 separate
       unsigned char arrays for red, green and blue, use an array of RGB
       structs.  this helps a tiny bit when rendering large images, since
       the data is always accessed in a linear manner (this improving
       processor cache performance)

 lib/Display.cc |  23 +-
 lib/Image.cc	| 687 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++---------------------
 lib/Image.hh	|  15 +-
 3 files changed, 442 insertions(+), 283 deletions(-)

