commit da1a0b34c11c71a993eafc16352e6c00889dfa34
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Tue Jan 7 16:06:01 2003 +0000

    multiple timers should be able to fire to the same timeout handler.

    accomplish this by sending the fired timer to the timeout() function
    in the timeout handler interface.  with this, we don't have to create
    small nested classes for each timer we create, we can simply use a
    single timeout handler subclass, and check the parameter against known
    timers.

