commit 38f270a30f1c3da1cf755a773271b1f8df6fcc2a
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Wed Nov 20 20:21:14 2002 +0000

    move the GCCache out of the public API.  use Pen instead.

    Pen now has it's own header/implementation file, and has an API
    similar to that of Color (ie. not requiring a Display argument, just a
    screen).

    the GCCache will be created on Display creation, and destroyed on
    Display destruction.

    no real changes have been made to the GCCache code. only the file name
    has been changed.

 lib/GCCache.cc | 207 ----------------------------------
 lib/GCCache.hh | 143 ------------------------
 lib/Pen.cc	| 318 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 lib/Pen.hh	|  62 +++++++++++
 4 files changed, 380 insertions(+), 350 deletions(-)

commit 69a1a68a2594f2334e1538195953579426d583f8
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Wed Nov 20 20:16:59 2002 +0000

    lots of cleanups and fixes to make 8bpp work again.

    for the moment, 8bpp default to ordered dither (this will be
    configurable in the future).  this dither has been expanded to give a
    bit better quality with a 16x16 dither matrix (instead of 8x8).

    one big difference now is that we should be able to support ALL
    possible color depths/visuals.  testing is needed to confirm this.

    also, we no longer allocate the color cube at startup.  instead, we
    just query the existing colors and use the closest matches we find.
    this has actually proven to be much better than the old approach: my X
    server comes up with the colormap already preallocated with the
    standard web palette (6x6x6 color cube).  the image quality is great,
    and we don't use up too many colors.  because of this, i have changed
    the default colorsPerChannel to 6 now (instead of 4).  i will need to
    test this on other 8bpp X servers (completeness).

    all code using Pens now use the new Pen API (commit to follow).

    oh, and i fixed the whiteline bug with crossdiagonal gradients :)

 lib/Image.cc | 280 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++----------------------
 1 file changed, 169 insertions(+), 111 deletions(-)

commit d05c75bb3ecd94430ce2c34c0b67f515445351a3
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Wed Nov 20 20:11:06 2002 +0000

    API revisions and code cleanups.

    the FontCache is modelled after the ColorCache.  it will be created on
    Display creation and destroyed on Display destruction.

    a font no longer requires a Display object.  the object is owned by
    the cache instead, so bt::Font becomes a wrapper, essentially.  this
    makes the API ligher and more straight forward, and reduces the amount
    of work needed to get a font loaded.

 lib/Font.cc | 353 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-----------------
 lib/Font.hh |	67 +++--------
 2 files changed, 260 insertions(+), 160 deletions(-)

commit 3d698821f4e379d54136309d6f570043579c6282
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Wed Nov 20 20:08:48 2002 +0000

    API revisions and code updates.

    the color cache is created at Display creation, and we use this to do
    all allocations.  this means we no longer need to pass the display
    argument to the pixel() function.

 lib/Color.cc | 117 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++---------------
 lib/Color.hh |   9 ++---
 2 files changed, 88 insertions(+), 38 deletions(-)

commit 236f7977b1a7cadab1b85706dd94e864e22b91db
Author: shaleh <shaleh>
Date:	Fri Nov 1 19:03:32 2002 +0000

