commit b7d31b60d7fe0af136d8af22ba439448698b4204
Author: shaleh <shaleh>
Date:	Thu Oct 10 22:07:41 2002 +0000

    From the bug report:
    When resizing a window, if you resize past the far edge
    of whatever window you're on, the window jumps to (what
    appears to be) your screen width. To reproduce: open
    up a window (even an ol' xterm will do), grab the right
    resize handle, pull it past the handle on the left, and
    enjoy. Works the other way too.

    The solution was two fold.	1) we needed to cast the unsigned frame.margin
    to a signed value in constrain, 2) we needed to be sure we were NOT using
    a negative value for the width or height in motionNotifyEvent().

 src/Window.cc | 27 +++++++++++++++++++--------
 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

commit ce407bd4acb9304da56c4d38a162301d011d8062
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Thu Oct 10 15:40:26 2002 +0000

