commit 9f8b82853fa4559b80addcbd4f47f4d4799a27f9
Author: shaleh <shaleh>
Date:	Wed Oct 9 19:21:56 2002 +0000

    calling bevel on an Image with a height where: h = height - (border_width *
    2) - 2 will be a negative number causes a segfault due to unsigned wrap
    around and the later loops eating up the color pointers.  The code now
    checks that width and height are at least equal to 2.  The old bevel2
    code checked for width and height greater than 4.  However looking at
    the current bevel() function checking for 2 seems sufficient.

 lib/Image.cc | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

commit d24b52010353efa2290a1872ef230cbe940e123f
Author: shaleh <shaleh>
Date:	Wed Oct 9 19:13:15 2002 +0000

    Split old Display class into Application and Display.  Application is the
    TimerQueueManager, EventLoop manager and all around control structure.
    Display now is a thin wrapper around the X Display pointer, the ScreenInfo
    list and the GC cache.  Update the lib, blackbox and bsetroot to match.

    bsetroot now derives from TimerQueueManager (because of ImageControl's
    timer) and only contains an instance of Display.  blackbox now derives
    from Application.

