commit 639afa3602b2012abafc12f977152b463b2ff9f6
Author: shaleh <shaleh>
Date:	Tue Oct 8 00:52:28 2002 +0000

    removing the last workspace now moves the windows to workspace N -
    1 instead of iconifying them.  This behavior is required by the netwm spec.

 src/Screen.cc	  | 4 ++--
 src/Workspace.cc | 8 +++++---
 src/Workspace.hh | 2 +-
 3 files changed, 8 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

commit 9a6d057976428e01a04489b2a3a9efa5b7c1be0c
Author: shaleh <shaleh>
Date:	Mon Oct 7 22:47:14 2002 +0000

    struts no longer cause the screen to recalculate the available area.
    Instead a timer and a dirty flag is used.  The hope is this will cut down
    on work when several strut updates occur in a row.	I had originally only
    employed a dirty flag but this did not handle the case where nothing
    noticed the flag.  In particular if you move the slit or toolbar while
    you have maximized windows open the windows would not be notified until
    something tried to read the screen's area.

