commit 3f0c57ce121ee795d3f9451f48a2b0df34bd563c
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Tue Jun 25 11:21:50 2002 +0000

    1) when resizing a window with a minimumsize, but a width_inc or
       height_inc of 1, don't remove the minimum size from the size
       displayed to the user

    2) fix the configureRequest function to use the gravity when a client
       requests a new position.  blackbox now conforms completely to ICCCM
       4.1.2.3 and 4.1.5.  this involved rewriting the gravity functions
       to work on a Rect argument, instead of always working on the client
       and frame rects.

