commit 50bc8fc1b0a3928a6b36c4916fae32e88853d41d
Author: shaleh <shaleh>
Date:	Tue May 28 07:57:55 2002 +0000

    bug fixes:

    shade a window and move it, the rubberband lines match the shaded size.
    Now
    change blackbox's style, hit reconfigure, whichever.  Now when you move the
    shaded window the rubberband lines match the full size window.  This was
    caused by the upsize() method.  We now check for shaded state and set the
    height accordingly.

    another shade problem.  shade a window, maximize it, then unmaximize it.
    The
    new window size is premax_h which was set to the height of the shaded
    window.
    Similar to the fix for the problem above we now always use the client
    size for
    this calculation.

 src/Window.cc | 35 ++++++++++++++++++++++++-----------
 1 file changed, 24 insertions(+), 11 deletions(-)

commit eb88b386d7f56a5078b3f3f251b2006591f0d45b
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Mon May 27 08:52:41 2002 +0000

    since some managed windows can also be window group controllers,
    we need to make sure that we don't clobber the event mask for the
    managed window, and  when unmanaging such windows, we should also
    delete the window group.

