 TODO		  |  2 ++
 src/Util.hh	  | 14 +++++++-------
 src/Workspace.cc |  4 ++--
 3 files changed, 11 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)

commit dbae400bdb71a7fdb886fa861b64a4069771916e
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Tue May 14 15:19:36 2002 +0000

    add Click Raise option to turn on/off single click raising in SloppyFocus
      - readded the updateFocusModel() methods to make this work properly again

    add bool Rect::valid() const method for checking the validity of a rect

    remove BlackboxWindow::workspace_number - use blackbox_attrib.workspace
    instead

    the decorations and functions in BlackboxWindow now use enum bitflags
    instead
      of a struct of Bools.  This will save a few bytes per window.

    after the introduction of Rect, use it for BlackboxWindow's client
    and frame
      positions.  remove old frame/client geometry functions and replace with
      a single method to get the Rect

    fix the new smart placement algorithm.  there were off-by-one errors in
    calcSpaces() (although harmless).  the guts of calcSpaces was replaced
    by a simpler implementation using convenience methods provided by our Rect
    class (things not available in OpenBox's Rect). there were 2 typos in the
    column sorting methods... after this, the smartplacement is perfectly
    correct.

    remove the Blackbox::maskWindowEvents() mechanism... this is something that
    i added long long ago to try and optimize away LinkedList lookups, and it's
    not even used now...

