commit 91d3c2e3001a46e40e6fbb2d487604c9dfbfc07f
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Fri Apr 19 16:13:30 2002 +0000

    don't ignore focus events that happen during a grab, only focus changes
    as a
    result of a grab or ungrab... this keeps focus from going screwy when using
    bbkeys to switch workspaces

 src/blackbox.cc | 6 ++++--
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

commit f930c44e2a8ad22f8d0266b1fef0f5a5a54206e4
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Fri Apr 19 08:30:40 2002 +0000

    unbreak Slit clients with a little modification to the BlackboxWindow
    constructor... we shouldn't reparent to frame.plate until we are sure that
    this is not a slit client... however, to make sure that property
    notifies are
    received correctly, we need to select for propertynotifies on the client
    before checking any properties...

    also, since we need to make sure not to remove clients that are reparented
    to the slit (since we get the reparent event now that we select for
    substructurenotify on the root window).

 src/Window.cc	 | 33 +++++++++++++++------------------
 src/blackbox.cc |  2 +-
 2 files changed, 16 insertions(+), 19 deletions(-)

commit e3bb57d1167bdf50c023d92736e7c33e786faf11
Author: bradleyhughes <bradleyhughes>
Date:	Fri Apr 19 07:13:06 2002 +0000

    1) make click raise work in slopp and click focus modes... this meant
    removing
       the updateFocusModel members from BlackboxWindow and Workspace

    2) this is a pretty big change, and a pretty important one: ghost windows
       are fixed... no more empty windows lying around that you can't close
       or kill
       this involved changing the event mask on the root window and on the
       client window... the BlackboxWindow constructor needed to be reorganized
       to make sure that associateWindow() was called before any of the
       property
       getters... server grabs needed to be readded to 2 places where we unmap
       the client window but don't want the unmap notify

       shaleh, if you have questions about this change, let me know and i can
       go through it :)

